comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. 100 +200 (layer 11) µL T1. Pause after layer 10. Completed print with slight superficial defects. Channels closed.
next steps: Decrease of exposure time from 8 to 6 s.

comment: Global offset is -1.5. Rest run #1 +200 (layer 11) µL T1. Pause after layer 10. Completed print with more superficial defects than #1. Channels partially open/can be perfused.
next steps: Rinse ink vat with DPBS. Increase tartrazine conc. in ink from 1 mM to 2 mM. Adjust exposure time.

comment: Global offset is -1.5. 100 µL T2. Pause after layer 10. Only first layer and bits of following layers attached to printhead, rest stuck on FEP film -> delamination during printing -> exposure time after first layer too short.
next steps: Rinse ink vat with DPBS and remove stuck gel with spatula. Increase of exposure times.

comment: Global offset is -1.5. Rest run #1 +200 (layer 11) µL T2. Pause after layer 10: looking good. Complete print stuck in ink vat after printing -> detached after layer 10 -> adhesion to printhead too weak -> increase first layer exposure time
next steps: Rinse ink vat with DPBS and remove stuck gel with spatula. Increase of exposure times.

comment: Global offset is -1.5. Rest run #1 +200 (layer 11) µL T2. Pause after layer 10. Completed print with slightest superficial defects. Channels well-defined and well-perfusable.
next steps: Prepare more T2 and produce samples for mechanical and biological testing (Log220601-02).
